r part of two weeks grinding between roughly 111.20 and 112.00, unable to sustain any meaningful directional impulse. That congestion eventually gave way on 30 June with a sharp single-session push toward 112.50, and from there a broader recovery unfolded through the first half of July. The acceleration became more pronounced from 14 July onward, with the pair adding nearly 200 pips across two sessions before stalling in the 113.60\u2013113.90 area. That stall is significant: the prior reaction zone at 113.95 has registered four prior touches, making it one of the more well-defined supply areas on the daily chart. Above that, a further prior reaction zone sits at 114.33, a level that has turned price on three occasions. The pair has not yet convincingly tested either level on a closing basis, and the last three daily candles have printed progressively tighter ranges \u2014 a sign that momentum is fading rather than building at these heights.\n\nOn the H1 timeframe, the intraday picture adds texture to that narrative. Price spent much of the overnight and early European session in a narrow consolidation band around 113.38\u2013113.43, before a brief dip toward 113.11 during the early London hours \u2014 a test of the prior reaction zone at 113.21 that held broadly, with buyers absorbing the move. Since then, the hourly sequence has been one of steady, measured recovery, with each successive candle printing a marginally higher close and price now nudging the session high at 113.59. The recovery from the morning low is constructive in isolation, but the pair is now pressing against the same area that has contained it for several sessions.\n\nThe calendar is empty for today, which removes the prospect of a volatility catalyst in either direction during the remainder of the session. Without a data-driven impulse, price action is likely to remain technically driven, with the 113.95 prior reaction zone acting as the immediate ceiling and the 113.21 zone serving as the near-term structural reference to the downside.\n\nWhat would alter the read materially is a clean daily close above 113.95, which would shift the near-term picture in favour of the bulls and bring the 114.33 area into focus. Conversely, a decisive break and close beneath the 113.21 prior reaction zone would suggest the recovery from the June lows is losing structural integrity, with the 112.86 zone the next reference of note below. Until one of those scenarios plays out, the desk reads this as a range-bound situation at the upper end of a recovery move.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}